[~snemeth] I just tested the patch on a real Hadoop cluster. Seems to be working fine.

One thing I wish to change is this:
{noformat}
  private void logAndStdErr(Exception e, String msg) {
    LOG.error(msg, e);
    System.err.println(msg);
  }
{noformat}

We log the stack trace in every case. As we discussed, errors that we can detect and handle don't need it. I'd replace it with this:

{noformat}
  private void logAndStdErr(Exception e, String msg) {
    LOG.debug("Stack trace", e);
    LOG.error(msg);
    System.err.println(msg);
  }
{noformat}

So we only print the trace if debug logging is enabled.

